<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Genesis 5:1-32</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="50">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="32">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">This is the book of Adam’s history. In the day of God’s creating Adam he made him in the likeness of God.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Male and female he created them. After that he blessed them and called their name Man in the day of their being created.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And Adam lived on for a hundred and thirty years. Then he became father to a son in his likeness, in his image, and called his name Seth.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And the days of Adam after his fathering Seth came to be eight hundred years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">So all the days of Adam that he lived amounted to nine hundred and thirty years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And Seth lived on for a hundred and five years. Then he became father to E&acute;nosh.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And after his fathering E&acute;nosh Seth continued to live eight hundred and seven years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">So all the days of Seth amounted to nine hundred and twelve years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And E&acute;nosh lived on for ninety years. Then he became father to Ke&acute;nan.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And after his fathering Ke&acute;nan E&acute;nosh continued to live eight hundred and fifteen years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">So all the days of E&acute;nosh amounted to nine hundred and five years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And Ke&acute;nan lived on for seventy years. Then he became father to Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And after his fathering Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel Ke&acute;nan continued to live eight hundred and forty years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">So all the days of Ke&acute;nan amounted to nine hundred and ten years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel lived on for sixty-five years. Then he became father to Ja&acute;red.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And after his fathering Ja&acute;red Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel continued to live eight hundred and thirty years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">So all the days of Ma&middot;hal&acute;a&middot;lel amounted to eight hundred and ninety-five years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And Ja&acute;red lived on for a hundred and sixty-two years. Then he became father to E&acute;noch.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And after his fathering E&acute;noch Ja&acute;red continued to live eight hundred years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">So all the days of Ja&acute;red amounted to nine hundred and sixty-two years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And E&acute;noch lived on for sixty-five years. Then he became father to Me&middot;thu&acute;se&middot;lah.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And after his fathering Me&middot;thu&acute;se&middot;lah E&acute;noch went on walking with the [true] God three hundred years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">So all the days of E&acute;noch amounted to three hundred and sixty-five years.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And E&acute;noch kept walking with the [true] God. Then he was no more, for God took him.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And Me&middot;thu&acute;se&middot;lah lived on for a hundred and eighty-seven years. Then he became father to La&acute;mech.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And after his fathering La&acute;mech Me&middot;thu&acute;se&middot;lah continued to live seven hundred and eighty-two years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">So all the days of Me&middot;thu&acute;se&middot;lah amounted to nine hundred and sixty-nine years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And La&acute;mech lived on for a hundred and eighty-two years. Then he became father to a son.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And he proceeded to call his name Noah, saying: “This one will bring us comfort from our work and from the pain of our hands resulting from the ground which Jehovah has cursed.”</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">And after his fathering Noah La&acute;mech continued to live five hundred and ninety-five years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">So all the days of La&acute;mech amounted to seven hundred and seventy-seven years and he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And Noah got to be five hundred years old. After that Noah became father to Shem, Ham and Ja&acute;pheth.</span>
</p>
</form>

