<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Genesis 11:1-32</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="50">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="32">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now all the earth continued to be of one language and of one set of words.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And it came about that in their journeying eastward they eventually discovered a valley plain in the land of Shi&acute;nar, and they took up dwelling there.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And they began to say, each one to the other: “Come on! Let us make bricks and bake them with a burning process.” So brick served as stone for them, but bitumen served as mortar for them.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">They now said: “Come on! Let us build ourselves a city and also a tower with its top in the heavens, and let us make a celebrated name for ourselves, for fear we may be scattered over all the surface of the earth.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And Jehovah proceeded to go down to see the city and the tower that the sons of men had built.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">After that Jehovah said: “Look! They are one people and there is one language for them all, and this is what they start to do. Why, now there is nothing that they may have in mind to do that will be unattainable for them.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Come now! Let us go down and there confuse their language that they may not listen to one another’s language.”</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Accordingly Jehovah scattered them from there over all the surface of the earth, and they gradually left off building the city.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">That is why its name was called Ba&acute;bel, because there Jehovah had confused the language of all the earth, and Jehovah had scattered them from there over all the surface of the earth.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">This is the history of Shem.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs10-2">Shem was a hundred years old when he became father to Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad two years after the deluge.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And after his fathering Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad Shem continued to live five hundred years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad lived thirty-five years. Then he became father to She&acute;lah.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And after his fathering She&acute;lah Ar&middot;pach&acute;shad continued to live four hundred and three years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And She&acute;lah lived thirty years. Then he became father to E&acute;ber.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And after his fathering E&acute;ber She&acute;lah continued to live four hundred and three years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And E&acute;ber lived on for thirty-four years. Then he became father to Pe&acute;leg.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And after his fathering Pe&acute;leg E&acute;ber continued to live four hundred and thirty years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And Pe&acute;leg lived on for thirty years. Then he became father to Re&acute;u.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And after his fathering Re&acute;u Pe&acute;leg continued to live two hundred and nine years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And Re&acute;u lived on for thirty-two years. Then he became father to Se&acute;rug.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And after his fathering Se&acute;rug Re&acute;u continued to live two hundred and seven years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And Se&acute;rug lived on for thirty years. Then he became father to Na&acute;hor.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And after his fathering Na&acute;hor Se&acute;rug continued to live two hundred years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And Na&acute;hor lived on for twenty-nine years. Then he became father to Te&acute;rah.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And after his fathering Te&acute;rah Na&acute;hor continued to live a hundred and nineteen years. Meanwhile he became father to sons and daughters.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And Te&acute;rah lived on for seventy years, after which he became father to A&acute;bram, Na&acute;hor and Ha&acute;ran.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And this is the history of Te&acute;rah.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs27-2">Te&acute;rah became father to A&acute;bram, Na&acute;hor and Ha&acute;ran; and Ha&acute;ran became father to Lot.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Later Ha&acute;ran died while in company with Te&acute;rah his father in the land of his birth, in Ur of the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And A&acute;bram and Na&acute;hor proceeded to take wives for themselves. The name of A&acute;bram’s wife was Sar&acute;ai, while the name of Na&acute;hor’s wife was Mil&acute;cah, the daughter of Ha&acute;ran, the father of Mil&acute;cah and father of Is&acute;cah.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">But Sar&acute;ai continued to be barren; she had no child.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">After that Te&acute;rah took A&acute;bram his son and Lot, the son of Ha&acute;ran, his grandson, and Sar&acute;ai his daughter-in-law, the wife of A&acute;bram his son, and they went with him out of Ur of the Chal&middot;de&acute;ans to go to the land of Ca&acute;naan. In time they came to Ha&acute;ran and took up dwelling there.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And the days of Te&acute;rah came to be two hundred and five years. Then Te&acute;rah died in Ha&acute;ran.</span>
</p>
</form>

