<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Genesis 12:1-20</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="50">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="20">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And Jehovah proceeded to say to A&acute;bram: “Go your way out of your country and from your relatives and from the house of your father to the country that I shall show you;</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">and I shall make a great nation out of you and I shall bless you and I will make your name great; and prove yourself a blessing.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And I will bless those who bless you, and him that calls down evil upon you I shall curse, and all the families of the ground will certainly bless themselves by means of you.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">At that A&acute;bram went just as Jehovah had spoken to him, and Lot went with him. And A&acute;bram was seventy-five years old when he went out from Ha&acute;ran.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">So A&acute;bram took Sar&acute;ai his wife and Lot the son of his brother and all the goods that they had accumulated and the souls whom they had acquired in Ha&acute;ran, and they got on their way out to go to the land of Ca&acute;naan. Finally they came to the land of Ca&acute;naan.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And A&acute;bram went on through the land as far as the site of She&acute;chem, near the big trees of Mo&acute;reh; and at that time the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ite was in the land.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Jehovah now appeared to A&acute;bram and said: “To your seed I am going to give this land.” After that he built an altar there to Jehovah, who had appeared to him.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Later he moved from there to the mountainous region to the east of Beth&acute;el and pitched his tent with Beth&acute;el on the west and A&acute;i on the east. Then he built an altar there to Jehovah and began to call on the name of Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Afterward A&acute;bram broke camp, going then from encampment to encampment toward the Neg&acute;eb.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Now a famine arose in the land and A&acute;bram made his way down toward Egypt to reside there as an alien, because the famine was severe in the land.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And it came about that as soon as he got near to entering Egypt, then he said to Sar&acute;ai his wife: “Please, now! I well know you are a woman beautiful in appearance.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">So it is bound to happen that the Egyptians will see you and will say, ‘This is his wife.’ And they will certainly kill me, but you they will preserve alive.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Please say you are my sister, in order that it may go well with me on your account, and my soul will be certain to live due to you.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">So it happened that, as soon as A&acute;bram entered Egypt, the Egyptians got to see the woman, that she was very beautiful.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And the princes of Phar&acute;aoh also got to see her and they began praising her to Phar&acute;aoh, so that the woman was taken to the house of Phar&acute;aoh.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And he treated A&acute;bram well on her account, and he came to have sheep and cattle and asses and menservants and maidservants and she-asses and camels.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Then Jehovah touched Phar&acute;aoh and his household with great plagues because of Sar&acute;ai, A&acute;bram’s wife.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">With that Phar&acute;aoh called A&acute;bram and said: “What is this you have done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife?</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Why did you say, ‘She is my sister,’ so that I was about to take her as my wife? And now here is your wife. Take her and go!”</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And Phar&acute;aoh issued commands to men concerning him, and they went escorting him and his wife and all that he had.</span>
</p>
</form>

