<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Genesis 13:1-18</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="50">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="18">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Following that A&acute;bram went up out of Egypt, he and his wife and all that he had, and Lot with him, to the Neg&acute;eb.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And A&acute;bram was heavily stocked with herds and silver and gold.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And he made his way from encampment to encampment out of the Neg&acute;eb and to Beth&acute;el, to the place where his tent had been at first between Beth&acute;el and A&acute;i,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">to the place of the altar that he had made there originally; and A&acute;bram proceeded to call there on the name of Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Now Lot, who was going along with A&acute;bram, also owned sheep and cattle and tents.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So the land did not allow for them to dwell all together, because their goods had become many and they were not able to dwell all together.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And a quarrel arose between the herders of A&acute;bram’s livestock and the herders of Lot’s livestock; and at that time the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ite and the Per&acute;iz&middot;zite were dwelling in the land.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Hence A&acute;bram said to Lot: “Please, do not let any quarreling continue between me and you and between my herdsmen and your herdsmen, for we men are brothers.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Is not the whole land available to you? Please, separate from me. If you go to the left, then I will go to the right; but if you go to the right, then I will go to the left.”</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">So Lot raised his eyes and saw the whole District of the Jordan, that all of it was a well-watered region before Jehovah brought Sod&acute;om and Go&middot;mor&acute;rah to ruin, like the garden of Jehovah, like the land of Egypt as far as Zo&acute;ar.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Then Lot chose for himself the whole District of the Jordan, and Lot moved his camp to the east. So they separated the one from the other.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">A&acute;bram dwelt in the land of Ca&acute;naan, but Lot dwelt among the cities of the District. Finally he pitched tent near Sod&acute;om.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And the men of Sod&acute;om were bad and were gross sinners against Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And Jehovah said to A&acute;bram after Lot had separated from him: “Raise your eyes, please, and look from the place where you are, northward and southward and eastward and westward,</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">because all the land at which you are looking, to you and to your seed I am going to give it until time indefinite.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And I will constitute your seed like the dust particles of the earth, so that, if a man could be able to count the dust particles of the earth, then your seed could be numbered.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Get up, go about in the land through its length and through its breadth, because to you I am going to give it.”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">So A&acute;bram continued to live in tents. Later on he came and dwelt among the big trees of Mam&acute;re, which are in He&acute;bron; and there he proceeded to build an altar to Jehovah.</span>
</p>
</form>

