<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Genesis 35:1-29</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="50">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="29">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">After that God said to Jacob: “Rise, go up to Beth&acute;el and dwell there, and make an altar there to the [true] God who appeared to you when you were running away from E&acute;sau your brother.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Then Jacob said to his household and to all who were with him: “Put away the foreign gods that are in the midst of <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> and cleanse yourselves and change <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> mantles,</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">and let us rise and go up to Beth&acute;el. And there I shall make an altar to the [true] God who answered me in the day of my distress in that he proved to be with me in the way that I have gone.”</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">So they gave Jacob all the foreign gods that were in their hands and the earrings that were in their ears, and Jacob hid them under the big tree that was close by She&acute;chem.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">After that they pulled away, and the terror of God came to be upon the cities that were round about them, so that they did not chase after the sons of Jacob.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Eventually Jacob came to Luz, which is in the land of Ca&acute;naan, that is to say, Beth&acute;el, he and all the people who were with him.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Then he built an altar there and began to call the place El-beth&acute;el, because there the [true] God had revealed himself to him at the time of his running away from his brother.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Later Deb&acute;o&middot;rah the nursing woman of Re&middot;bek&acute;ah died and was buried at the foot of Beth&acute;el under a massive tree. Hence he called its name Al&acute;lon-bac&acute;uth.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">God now appeared to Jacob once again during his coming from Pad&acute;dan-a&acute;ram and blessed him.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">And God went on to say to him: “Your name is Jacob. No longer is your name to be called Jacob, but Israel will your name become.” And he began to call his name Israel.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And God said further to him: “I am God Almighty. Be fruitful and become many. Nations and a congregation of nations will proceed out of you, and kings will come out of your loins.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">As for the land that I have given to Abraham and to Isaac, to you I shall give it, and to your seed after you I shall give the land.”</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">After that God went up from above him at the place where he had spoken with him.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Consequently Jacob stationed a pillar in the place where he had spoken with him, a pillar of stone, and he poured a drink offering upon it and poured oil upon it.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Jacob continued to call the name of the place where God had spoken with him Beth&acute;el.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Then they pulled away from Beth&acute;el. And while there was yet a good stretch of land before coming to Eph&acute;rath, Rachel proceeded to give birth, and it was going hard with her in making the delivery.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">But so it was that while she had difficulty in making the delivery the midwife said to her: “Do not be afraid, for you will have this son also.”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And the result was that as her soul was going out (because she died) she called his name Ben-o&acute;ni; but his father called him Benjamin.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Thus Rachel died and was buried on the way to Eph&acute;rath, that is to say, Beth&acute;le&middot;hem.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">Hence Jacob stationed a pillar over her grave. This is the pillar of Rachel’s grave down to this day.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">After that Israel pulled away and pitched his tent a distance beyond the tower of E&acute;der.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And it came about while Israel was tabernacling in that land that once Reu&acute;ben went and lay down with Bil&acute;hah his father’s concubine, and Israel got to hear of it.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs22-2">So there came to be twelve sons of Jacob.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">The sons by Le&acute;ah were Jacob’s firstborn Reu&acute;ben and Sim&acute;e&middot;on and Le&acute;vi and Judah and Is&acute;sa&middot;char and Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">The sons by Rachel were Joseph and Benjamin.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And the sons by Bil&acute;hah, Rachel’s maidservant, were Dan and Naph&acute;ta&middot;li.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And the sons by Zil&acute;pah, Le&acute;ah’s maidservant, were Gad and Ash&acute;er. These are Jacob’s sons who were born to him in Pad&acute;dan-a&acute;ram.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">At length Jacob came to Isaac his father to Mam&acute;re, to Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-ar&acute;ba, that is to say, He&acute;bron, where Abraham and also Isaac had resided as aliens.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And the days of Isaac came to be a hundred and eighty years.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">After that Isaac expired and died and was gathered to his people, old and satisfied with days, and E&acute;sau and Jacob his sons buried him.</span>
</p>
</form>

